        "m_strFirstSentence": "These are classic symptoms of cataracts. Currently, surgery is the only effective way to improve your vision. The procedure takes about 10 to 15 minutes and is usually done under local anesthesia. You can generally return for a follow up the very next day. While the risk is relatively low, potential complications like infection or inflammation can occur. After surgery, it is vital to follow medical advice, use your eye drops as scheduled, and avoid strenuous exercise to ensure proper healing. Next, I will introduce you to the different types of lens surgery.",
